'''人民量化寬鬆'''（{{lang|en|People's Quantitative Easing}}，簡稱'''PQE'''），在2015年，由英國工黨[[2015年工党_(英国)领袖选举|黨魁候選人]][[杰里米·科爾賓|傑瑞米·柯賓]]提出，此政策要求[[英格蘭銀行|英格蘭銀行]]印製鈔票給政府投資。這項政策佔據了許多媒體版面，有的認為這政策不符合現行經濟運作<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/13/yvette-cooper-jeremy-corbyn-policies-not-credible-labour|title=Yvette Cooper says Labour rival Jeremy Corbyn's policies not credible or radical|last=|first=|date=2015-08-13|work=The Guardian|access-date=|via=|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128112355/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/13/yvette-cooper-jeremy-corbyn-policies-not-credible-labour|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-33884836 |title=Would Corbyn's 'QE for people' float or sink Britain? |work=BBC News |date=2015-08-12 |accessdate=2016-12-24 |archive-date=2015-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150818102547/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-33884836 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，有的替它辯護<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/14/the-labour-party-stands-at-a-crossroads|title=The Labour party stands at a crossroads|last=|first=|date=2015-08-14|work=The Guardian|access-date=|via=|archive-date=2019-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223004738/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/14/the-labour-party-stands-at-a-crossroads|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/sep/04/corbynomics-radical-mainstream-economic-orthodoxy|title=Corbynomics sounds subversive, but maybe not for long|last=Clark|first=Tom|date=2015-09-04|work=The Guardian|access-date=|via=|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108110325/http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/sep/04/corbynomics-radical-mainstream-economic-orthodoxy|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==政策==
柯賓的PQE中提到，投資房地產與大眾運輸的費用，需由[[英格蘭銀行|英格蘭銀行]]印製。藉由此政策達到兩個效果：
#將英國的經濟系統推向一個高技術、高科技的新紀元。
#建造更多公有住宅，減少長期下來住宅津貼的支出。為了達到此目的，英格蘭銀行需購買債券，籌設一所國營的投資銀行<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.londonlovesbusiness.com/business-news/politics/corbynomics-what-on-earth-is-jeremy-corbyns-economic-policy/10787.article |title=Corbynomics - what on earth is Jeremy Corbyn's economic policy? |accessdate=2016-12-24 |archive-date=2015-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150911032546/http://www.londonlovesbusiness.com/business-news/politics/corbynomics-what-on-earth-is-jeremy-corbyns-economic-policy/10787.article |dead-url=yes }}. London Loves Business. Retrieved on 12 September 2015.</ref><ref name=telegraph-20150913>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/11862318/What-are-we-to-think-of-Jeremy-Corbyns-peoples-QE.html |title=What are we to think of Jeremy Corbyn's 'people's QE'? |first=Roger |last=Bootle |authorlink=Roger Bootle |newspaper=Daily Telegraph |date=2015-09-13 |accessdate=2015-09-17 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108092411/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/11862318/What-are-we-to-think-of-Jeremy-Corbyns-peoples-QE.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

此政策的靈感源自於政治經濟學者{{tsl|en|Richard Murphy (political economist)|理查·墨菲 (政經學家)|理查·墨菲}}<ref name="guardian-20150922">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/sep/22/richard-murphy-corbynomics-tax-social-housing-britain |title=Can Corbynomics guru Richard Murphy fix Britain? |author=Zoe Williams |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2015-09-22 |accessdate=2015-09-23 |archive-date=2020-12-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205010740/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/sep/22/richard-murphy-corbynomics-tax-social-housing-britain |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但墨菲表明了，這是適用於2020年的政策，而且，前提是，持續實施傳統的量化寬鬆的狀況下，經濟情況依舊是低通貨膨脹、低利率、高失業、低薪資。如果經濟快速成長，PQE就不需要，因為成長的稅收便足以支付必要的投資<ref name=theaccountant-20150824>{{cite news |url=http://www.theaccountant-online.com/features/corbynomics-everything-you-always-wanted-to-know-about-it-explained-by-richard-murphy-4654295/ |title=Corbynomics: Everything you always wanted to know about it, explained by Richard Murphy |author=Carlos Martin Tornero |newspaper=The Accountant |date=2015-08-24 |accessdate=2015-09-26 |archive-date=2017-05-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170530182038/http://www.theaccountant-online.com/features/corbynomics-everything-you-always-wanted-to-know-about-it-explained-by-richard-murphy-4654295/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===與直昇機撒錢的不同===

經濟學教授{{tsl|en|Simon Wren-Lewis|西蒙·雷恩路易斯}}解釋了PQE與[[米爾頓·佛利民|米爾頓·佛利民]]提出的「直升機撒錢」（也稱「專為人民訂造的量化寬鬆」<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blogs.reuters.com/anatole-kaletsky/2012/08/01/how-about-quantitative-easing-for-the-people/|title=How about quantitative easing for the people?|last=Kaletsky|first=Anatole|date=2012-08-01|website=Reuters Blogs|publisher=|access-date=2016-10-06|archive-date=2013-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130528204341/http://blogs.reuters.com/anatole-kaletsky/2012/08/01/how-about-quantitative-easing-for-the-people/|dead-url=no}}</ref>）的不同。「直升機撒錢」，由中央銀行分配內部最新印製的貨幣給各個銀行，而且，製造的消費需求，政府皆不干預。然而，PQE金融投資計畫，在某一層度是由政府發起的。所以PQE影響了中央銀行的獨立原則<ref name=srw-20150816>{{cite web |url=http://mainlymacro.blogspot.co.uk/2015/08/peoples-qe-and-corbyns-qe.html |title=People's QE and Corbyn's QE |author={{tsl|en|Simon Wren-Lewis||Simon Wren-Lewis}} |publisher=mainly macro |date=2015-08-16 |accessdate=2015-09-20 |archive-date=2017-12-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208171243/https://mainlymacro.blogspot.co.uk/2015/08/peoples-qe-and-corbyns-qe.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 反響 ==
此政策被其他黨魁候選人批評為經濟白癡<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/13/yvette-cooper-jeremy-corbyn-policies-not-credible-labour|title=Yvette Cooper says Labour rival Jeremy Corbyn's policies not credible or radical|accessdate=2016-12-24|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128112355/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/13/yvette-cooper-jeremy-corbyn-policies-not-credible-labour|dead-url=no}}</ref>，也造成在英國投資的風險<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-33884836|title=Would Corbyn's 'QE for people' float or sink Britain?|date=2015-08-12|work=BBC News|accessdate=2016-12-24|archive-date=2015-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150818102547/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-33884836|dead-url=no}}</ref>。歐盟里斯本條約第123條明文禁止中央銀行印製鈔票以支應政府支出，英國此舉將違反該法條，而吃上歐盟法院的官司<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/bank-of-england/11804324/Jeremy-Corbyns-Peoples-QE-would-force-Britain-into-three-year-battle-with-the-EU.html |title=Jeremy Corbyn's 'People's QE' would force Britain into three-year battle with the EU |location=London |work=The Daily Telegraph |first=Peter |last=Spence |date=2015-08-15 |accessdate=2016-12-24 |archive-date=2016-04-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424124949/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/bank-of-england/11804324/Jeremy-Corbyns-Peoples-QE-would-force-Britain-into-three-year-battle-with-the-EU.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=http://www.lisbon-treaty.org/wcm/the-lisbon-treaty/treaty-on-the-functioning-of-the-european-union-and-comments/part-3-union-policies-and-internal-actions/title-viii-economic-and-monetary-policy/chapter-1-economic-policy/391-article-123.html |title=The Lisbon Treaty Article 123 |access-date=2016-12-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150822111902/http://www.lisbon-treaty.org/wcm/the-lisbon-treaty/treaty-on-the-functioning-of-the-european-union-and-comments/part-3-union-policies-and-internal-actions/title-viii-economic-and-monetary-policy/chapter-1-economic-policy/391-article-123.html |archive-date=2015-08-22 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。[[每日电讯报|每日電訊報]]寫道，量化寬鬆政策可能導致通貨膨脹。當今，英格蘭銀行緊抓著銀行內部的錢，因而顛倒了此政策中地方與中央的關係，然而，這權力卻帶來了抗衡量化寬鬆的效果。但是，如果錢流入了中央投資銀行的話，通貨膨脹的問題可能更難解決<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/11862318/What-are-we-to-think-of-Jeremy-Corbyns-peoples-QE.html |title=What are we to think of Jeremy Corbyn's 'people’s QE'? |accessdate=2016-12-24 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108092411/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/11862318/What-are-we-to-think-of-Jeremy-Corbyns-peoples-QE.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2015年8月3號，英國工黨的影子內閣之一的[[克里斯·萊斯利|克里斯·萊斯利]]評論這個政策會招來通貨膨脹與利息升高<ref name="guardian-20150803">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/03/jeremy-corbyn-economic-strategy-would-keep-tories-in-power-chris-leslie|title=Corbyn's economic strategy would keep Tories in power, top Labour figure says|date=2015-08-03|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=2015-09-20|author=Nicholas Watt|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108144746/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/03/jeremy-corbyn-economic-strategy-would-keep-tories-in-power-chris-leslie|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

然而；經濟學家{{tsl|en|Robert Skidelsky|羅伯特·斯基德爾斯基|}}認同由國家投資銀行執行的量化寬鬆政策<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/14/the-labour-party-stands-at-a-crossroads|title=The Labour party stands at a crossroads|last=|first=|date=2015-08-14|work=The Guardian|via=|access-date=|archive-date=2019-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223004738/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/14/the-labour-party-stands-at-a-crossroads|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="guardian-20150819">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2015/aug/19/corbynomics-why-we-should-take-it-seriously|title=Why we should take Corbynomics seriously|last=|first=Robert|date=2015-08-19|work=|newspaper=The Guardian|via=|accessdate=2015-09-20|access-date=|author=Skidelsky|archive-date=2015-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150919080033/http://www.theguardian.com/business/2015/aug/19/corbynomics-why-we-should-take-it-seriously|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而且[[衛報|衛報]]與[[金融時報|金融時報]]雙雙刊登了對量化寬鬆有利的文章<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ftalphaville.ft.com/2015/08/06/2136475/corbyns-peoples-qe-could-actually-be-a-decent-idea/|title=Corby's "People's QE" could actually be a decent idea|accessdate=2015-08-20|date=2015-08-06|last=Klein|first=Matthew|website=Financial Times Alphaville|archive-date=2020-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124101833/https://ftalphaville.ft.com/2015/08/06/2136475/corbyns-peoples-qe-could-actually-be-a-decent-idea/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/sep/04/corbynomics-radical-mainstream-economic-orthodoxy|title=Corbynomics sounds subversive, but maybe not for long|last=Clark|first=Tom|date=2015-09-04|work=The Guardian|via=|access-date=|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108110325/http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/sep/04/corbynomics-radical-mainstream-economic-orthodoxy|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[伯明翰大学|伯明翰大學]]經濟學者東尼·葉慈（Tony Yates）在衛報上刊登了一篇有關量化寬鬆的評論。東尼·葉慈建議政府在選前魯莽的印錢花費並在大選後重新緊縮財務促成大量的通貨膨脹。葉慈更進一步擔憂高通貨膨脹以及經濟的不穩定很難使窮苦人家受益<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/economics-blog/2015/sep/22/jeremy-corbyn-qe-for-the-people-jeopardises-bank-of-england-independence|title=Corbyn's QE for the people jeopardises the Bank of England's independence|last=Yates|first=Tony|date=2015-09-22|work=|newspaper=The Guardian|via=|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|access-date=2016-10-06|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108113501/http://www.theguardian.com/business/economics-blog/2015/sep/22/jeremy-corbyn-qe-for-the-people-jeopardises-bank-of-england-independence|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[獨立報|獨立報]]則登出一篇文章爭論適量使用人民量化寬鬆政策將有效的提升就業率、通貨膨脹以及減少自[[2007年–2008年環球金融危機|2008年金融海嘯]]以來的債務負擔<ref name="independent-20150915">{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/voices/comment/peoples-quantitative-easing-may-be-the-best-way-to-undo-the-mistakes-of-the-first-round-of-qe-10501479.html|title=People's Quantitative Easing may be the best way to undo the mistakes of the first round of QE|date=2015-09-15|newspaper=The Independent|accessdate=2015-09-19|author=George Cooper|archive-date=2018-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180727024231/https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/comment/peoples-quantitative-easing-may-be-the-best-way-to-undo-the-mistakes-of-the-first-round-of-qe-10501479.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

每日電訊報的報導指出，[[匯豐銀行|匯豐銀行]]首席經濟顧問史蒂芬·金（Stephen King）和[[標準人壽|標準人壽]]的高階國際財務顧問傑里米·勞森（Jeremy Lawson）皆指出當經濟進入下一個低迷期，且傳統[[量化寬鬆|量化寬鬆]]政策無效時，他們會支持使用人民量化寬鬆政策<ref name="telegraph-20150916">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/11869701/Jeremy-Corbyns-QE-for-the-people-is-exactly-what-the-world-may-soon-need.html|title=Jeremy Corbyn's QE for the people is exactly what the world may soon need|last=Evans-Pritchard|first=Ambrose|date=2015-09-16|authorlink=Ambrose Evans-Pritchard|newspaper=Daily Telegraph|accessdate=2015-09-17|archive-date=2021-01-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210131163952/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/11869701/Jeremy-Corbyns-QE-for-the-people-is-exactly-what-the-world-may-soon-need.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年8月柯賓聲明他從經濟學家的元老[[保羅·克魯格曼|保羅·克魯格曼]]和[[约瑟夫·斯蒂格利茨|約瑟夫·斯蒂格利茨]]那裏得到了該政策原則上的支持<ref name="cnbc-20150818">{{cite news|url=http://www.cnbc.com/2015/08/18/peoples-qe-left-wing-leaders-plans-for-the-uk.html|title=.People's QE?. Left-wing leader's plans for the UK|date=2015-08-18|publisher=CNBC News|accessdate=2015-09-20|author=Catherine Boyle|archive-date=2020-12-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201228034155/https://www.cnbc.com/2015/08/18/peoples-qe-left-wing-leaders-plans-for-the-uk.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nyt-20150804">{{cite news|url=http://krugman.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/08/04/corbyn-and-the-cringe-caucus/|title=Corbyn and the Cringe Caucus|date=2015-08-04|newspaper=New York Times|accessdate=2015-09-20|author=Paul Krugman|archive-date=2020-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114144027/https://krugman.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/08/04/corbyn-and-the-cringe-caucus|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nyt-20150914">{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/14/opinion/paul-krugman-labours-dead-center.html|title=Labour's Dead Center|date=2015-09-14|newspaper=New York Times|accessdate=2015-09-20|author=Paul Krugman|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108120347/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/14/opinion/paul-krugman-labours-dead-center.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年9月27日在布萊頓舉行的{{tsl|en|Labour Party (UK) Conference|英國工黨大會|工黨大會}}上宣布成立{{tsl|en|Economic Advisory Committee|經濟諮詢委員會|}}，[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC新聞]]經濟學編輯[[羅伯特·佩斯頓|羅伯特·佩斯頓]]認為該委員會的{{tsl|en|Simon Wren-Lewis||Simon Wren-Lewis}}和[[約瑟夫·史迪格里茲|約瑟夫·史迪格里茲]]是一個政策趨向保守的象徵。羅伯特認為這些特定的經濟學家將促使政府走向「利用低利率借貸並投資基礎建設」的路；他們不會採納過於偏激的方式，因為他們害怕英國央行的反通膨立場被動搖。這個政策只適用的時機是將其當作雨傘一樣偶爾使用，不然經濟將會進入下一個大低迷<ref name="BBC01">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34376085|title=Corbynomics' Thatcher moment|accessdate=2016-03-11|date=2015-09-27|last=Peston|first=Robert|publisher=''[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]]''|website=|access-date=|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108110525/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34376085|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

20162月，全世界最大的基金公司{{tsl|en|Bridgewater Associates||Bridgewater Associates}}的創辦人[[雷·達利奧|雷·達利奧]]說隨著量化寬鬆功效減弱，接下來的貨幣以及財政政策應該包括央行更加積極的財政開支。政府的財政開支將會「貨幣化」<ref name=reuters-20160218>{{cite news |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-funds-bridgewater-dalio-idUSKCN0VR0EH |title=Bridgewater's Dalio: 'Helicopter money' might help U.S. economy |author=Jennifer Ablan |publisher=Reuters |date=2016-02-18 |accessdate=2016-02-19 |archive-date=2020-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026104001/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-funds-bridgewater-dalio-idUSKCN0VR0EH |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

